1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,200
Isaiah 15. The burden of Moab.

2
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:22,631
Because in the night Ar of Moab is laid waste, and brought to silence; because in the night Kir of Moab is laid waste, and brought to silence; He is gone up to Bajith, and to Dibon, the high places, to weep: Moab shall howl over Nebo, and over Medeba: on all their heads shall be baldness, and every beard cut off.

3
00:00:22,631 --> 00:00:31,560
In their streets they shall gird themselves with sackcloth: on the tops of their houses, and in their streets, every one shall howl, weeping abundantly.

4
00:00:31,560 --> 00:00:41,472
And Heshbon shall cry, and Elealeh: their voice shall be heard even unto Jahaz: therefore the armed soldiers of Moab shall cry out; his life shall be grievous unto him.

5
00:00:41,472 --> 00:00:54,168
My heart shall cry out for Moab; his fugitives shall flee unto Zoar, an heifer of three years old: for by the mounting up of Luhith with weeping shall they go it up; for in the way of Horonaim they shall raise up a cry of destruction.

6
00:00:54,168 --> 00:01:01,320
For the waters of Nimrim shall be desolate: for the hay is withered away, the grass faileth, there is no green thing.

7
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:07,872
Therefore the abundance they have gotten, and that which they have laid up, shall they carry away to the brook of the willows.

8
00:01:07,872 --> 00:01:15,024
For the cry is gone round about the borders of Moab; the howling thereof unto Eglaim, and the howling thereof unto Beer-elim.

9
00:01:15,024 --> 00:01:23,736
For the waters of Dimon shall be full of blood: for I will bring more upon Dimon, lions upon him that escapeth of Moab, and upon the remnant of the land.

